52.8	Ne-Yo	Ne-Yo	Shaffer Chimere Smith, Jr. (born October 18, 1979), better known by his stage name Ne-Yo, is a pop and R&amp;B singer-songwriter, record producer, dancer and actor. Beginning his career as a songwriter, Ne-Yo penned the hit "Let Me Love You" for singer Mario. The single's successful release in the United States prompted an informal meeting between Ne-Yo and Def Jam's label head, and signing a recording contract.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Ne-Yo_in_the_studio.jpg/220px-Ne-Yo_in_the_studio.jpg
